1. "Where the Crawdads Sing"
Author: Delia Owens
Description: A coming-of-age story set in the marshes of North Carolina, it follows Kya Clark, the "Marsh Girl," as she navigates loneliness, love, and a murder investigation.
Price: Approximately $15.99 (Paperback)
2. "The Midnight Library"
Author: Matt Haig
Description: A thought-provoking novel about a library that allows you to explore the different lives you could have lived, based on the choices you made.
Price: Approximately $16.00 (Paperback)
3. "The Vanishing Half"
Author: Brit Bennett
Description: This novel explores the lives of twin sisters who choose to live in two very different worlds—one black and one white—examining themes of identity and family.
Price: Approximately $17.00 (Paperback)
4. "Educated"
Author: Tara Westover
Description: A memoir detailing the author’s quest for knowledge, growing up in a strict and abusive household in rural Idaho, and her journey to earn a PhD from Cambridge University.
Price: Approximately $14.99 (Paperback)
5. "The Silent Patient"
Author: Alex Michaelides
Description: A psychological thriller about a woman who shoots her husband and then stops speaking, and the psychotherapist determined to uncover her motive.
Price: Approximately $16.99 (Paperback)
6. "Daisy Jones & The Six"
Author: Taylor Jenkins Reid
Description: A fictional oral history of a 1970s rock band, exploring the complexities of fame, love, and the music industry.
Price: Approximately $17.00 (Paperback)
7. "The Seven Husbands of Evelyn Hugo"
Author: Taylor Jenkins Reid
Description: A historical fiction novel about a reclusive Hollywood icon who recounts her glamorous and scandalous life to a young journalist.
Price: Approximately $16.99 (Paperback)
8. "Atomic Habits"
Author: James Clear
Description: A self-help book that provides strategies for building good habits and breaking bad ones, emphasizing the power of small changes.
Price: Approximately $24.99 (Hardcover)
9. "The Song of Achilles"
Author: Madeline Miller
Description: A retelling of the Iliad from the perspective of Patroclus, exploring his relationship with Achilles and the events of the Trojan War.
Price: Approximately $16.00 (Paperback)
10. "Circe"
Author: Madeline Miller
Description: A reimagining of the life of Circe, the enchantress from Greek mythology, exploring themes of power, identity, and transformation.
Price: Approximately $17.00 (Paperback)
